    <svcproc svcproctype="proctype" graphiccount="1">
        <title>REFERENCE VOLTAGE SENSORS</title>
        <para>Reference voltage sensors are supplied with a constant 5 volts regulated supplied by the ECM. A voltage
            regulator supplies the reference voltage (Vref) to these sensors. This voltage is changed by the sensor and
            the signal is relayed back to the ECM. The ECM, by comparing the Vref to the returned signal can check it's
            internal programmed tables to determine the value of the variable being measured.
        </para>
